Title: Littmann Classic II S.E. Smoke-Finish Chestpiece, Tube, 28 Inch, 2942 Acoustic Stethoscope(Dark Olive Green)
Description: The Littmann Classic II S.E. Stethoscope provides high acoustic sensitivity through its dual-sided, stainless steel chestpiece, featuring a tunable diaphragm on one side and a traditional bell function on the opposite side. The Classic II S.E. is used by students and medical professionals alike to identify, listen to, and study heart, lung, and other body sounds for physical assessment and diagnosis. Littmann tunable diaphragm technology and dual sided chestpiece deliver high acoustic sensitivity, versatility, and time-saving convenience. Switching between bell and diaphragm modes is as easy as a simple pressure change on the chestpiece, which means there is no need to remove, index and replace for same-site auscultation. Resilient tubing folds tightly for pocket portabilityand retains its shape while patented Snap Tight Soft-Sealing Eartips help form an effective acoustic seal. The anatomically correct headset is angled to channel sound and enhance listening comfort while the nonchill rim and diaphragm provide patient comfort. The Classic II SE is made in the USA. The product and package are latex-free and come with an alternate pair of small eartips and instructions.
